task.summary: Working towards a docker image that can actually run the flow tree executor.
Purged the init script of msched-specific code.
Some improvements to the handling of the default job factory, which for some reason was excluded from putting jobs into the pool. Also a lot of maven library files.
Removed archiva, as we now have a real instance in the cloud.
Updated Dockerfile to reflect new airflow design.
Working towards running airflow on flowtree.
Working towards a stable docker image for flowtree.
Use postgres for our airflow database.
Working toward a functioning postgres install.
Minor changes to build and deploy.
Migrated flow tree executor plugin install to init.py.
More customization of flow tree plugin.
Updated configuration to point at full path of FlowTreeExecutor.
Include a default queue for flow tree.
Expanding functionality of the flow tree command line.
Reorganized packages so that everything is now in io.flowtree.*
Migrated some flowtree code which was trapped in Rings project back into flowtree.
Introduced AWS code for supporting login via Cognito.
If AWS credentials are available, initialize CognitoLogin.
Use the OutputServer rather than the Client (which may not be initialized).
Added default parameters for starting resource distribution. Also, always start resource distribution.
Terminal is on by default. OutputServer is off by default. When loading a local file into DistributedResource, peel off the path and replace it with "/files/".
Do not exit if there is no config file for FlowTreeCliServer. Do not prompt user on System.in for Encryptor.
Upgraded to match renamed Chart type.
